article.headline: Mike Singletary's double-double fuels Texas Tech
article.story: LUBBOCK, Texas -- Mike Singletary had 29 points and 13 rebounds and Texas Tech held on for a 86-82 win over Oral Roberts on Tuesday night. John Roberson hit five free throws down the stretch for the Red Raiders (5-3), who had lost their last two games at the South Padre Invitational. Texas Tech is 5-0 at home this season. Singletary had his highest scoring game since his career-high 43 points against Texas A&M in March 2009. Robert Lewandowski had 17 points and Roberson 16, and Brad Reese added 12 for Texas Tech. Oral Roberts (2-4) took its first lead in the final minute of the first half, and the lead changed 13 times after halftime. Hunter McClintock led the Golden Eagles with 19 points while Warren Niles had 18.
